<TITLE> Fire deaths reach 119 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 7 (bdnews24.com)-- A woman has died from grave burns wounds from last week's devastating blaze in Old Dhaka, pushing the death counts to 119. Sakhina Khatun, 50, died between 11:30am and midday on Monday at the Combined Military Hospital in Dhaka, executive magistrate Rahima Begum said. Seven-year-old 'Sayem' died around 5pm on Sunday at the hospital. His mother Lipi Akhter is also undergoing treatment there. Khatun and 13 others were transferred from Dhaka Medical College Hospital on Friday. Twelve others are under treatment there. The DMCH, the country's biggest public hospital, has 25 patients at its burns and plastic unit now. The blaze on June 3 left more than 150 injured, mostly women and children. bd
